    <stitle>REYCO 101A, 102, 102W SUSPENSIONS - CLEAN AND INSPECT - TORQUE ARM BUSHING REPLACEMENT - REYCO 102
        SUSPENSION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TORQUE ARM BUSHING REPLACEMENT - REYCO 102 SUSPENSION</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two-piece torque arm bushings (Item 34) by removing the bolt from each, then
                working the two pieces away from the torque arm.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install the two-piece arm bushings, apply a thin coat of rubber lubricant to the outer
                diameter of the bushing. Use the torque arm bolt (Item 33) to pull the two bushing pieces together.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
